@node "About" "WHAT IS THIS GAME?"
Card Sharks is your basic game of High/Low played with cards.  Read the
in-game instructions for more info.

It was written for DLG - it WILL NOT WORK with any other BBS software!
@endnode

@node "Install" "Installation"
Installation is pretty simple - first copy the Sharks directory to your DOORS:
directory.  Then, make a directory called GameData in your Doors: directory.
After that, assign GameData: to Doors:Gamedata.

Then go to the DLG menu configuration setup.  Add a menu item that looks like
the following:

[ 1] Letter:                   C
[ 2] Executable: (path/name)   Doors:Sharks/Sharks "%NAME" %PORT %ANSI
[ 4] Description:              Card Sharks
[ 5] Type:                     Executable
[ 6] Help File:                doors/c
[ 7] Lower level:              5
[ 8] Upper level:              255
[ 9] Hidden:                   NO
[10] Load type:                OVERLAY
[11] Ask user if sure:         NO
[12] Pend messages:            YES
[13] Cli mode:                 NO
[14] Pause on completion:      NO
[15] Log value:                150
[16] Activity string:
[17] Priority:                 DEFAULT
[18] Edit help file

Select =>

That's all there is to it!
@endnode

@node "Contact" "How to reach the author!"
You have two ways of reaching me - Internet E-Mail or you can call a GREAT DLG
board in the Portland area (Fly By Night) and leave me an E-Mail message
there.  Ok, make that 3 ways, I have a snail-mail address as well that you can
send a message to me if you have to!

